The character i play is a Knight.<br>
A follower and chosen of Innoruuk.<br>
I am Orderly Evil but do not see myself as such (ie evil).<br>
<br>
I am not one to go around and /rude many chars, although it did happen (seeing Halfling camping the Nektulos guards can trigger that in me).<br>
I am Knight and i must stay honorable.<br>
I can kill you and stay honorable.<br>
I can slit the throat of a Koada`Dal child while staying honorable.<br>
<br>
I just try to stay in char most of the time, and that, at least for me, means :<br>
<br>
Obey and pay respect to the Church of Innorruk and its Priest (meaning i will obey almost any order/request from any Priest of the father i encounter, asking little or no questions about it).<br>
Obey and pay respect to the members of the Lodge of the Dead (meaning i will help/assist any Necromancer/Knight of the father i encounter, asking little or no questions about it).<br>
Help and assist my brothers and sisters of the Void for thay are the closest thing to a family this Knight ever had (i still have issues with the family concept though...)<br>
Help as many Tier`Dals i can whether young ones or elders. Some do not worship our Lord but we are all his children and he WILL judge us when he sees fit. Yes that does include the ones who lost faith.<br>
Try and assist the followers of the Gods that are &quot;allies&quot; to the Father (Cazic Thule, Rallos Zek, Bertoxxulous) or at least not ennemies.<br>
Fight the followers of the gods that oppose the Father (the wench Tunare, the Marr twins...).<br>
<br>
My character evolved and is now trying to appreciate chars on their acts, not on their words. When he was young he would not even speak to a non Tier`Dal, this has changed.<br>
I have learned that many serve the Father and his allies. It is not for me to judge if they are worthy or not. The Father will, i am just one of his chosen.<br>
<br>
Besides, I have lived/played things that make this character be a little more &quot;open&quot; minded (notice the quotes and NO i will not kiss and cuddle Halflings, my blade will). I have my issues and i walk a path (between Heaven and Hell, replace by the official Church of Innorruk terms here) towards redemption. No words will make things change, acts will. Acts and the faith in the Father.<br>
<br>
On a side note, i do not trades / accept ports ... or anything that comes from what i consider an enemy.  I can give away my unused items to allies but will never make a profit in selling them to lightskins. I am a Knight, not a merchant.<br>
I do not fight along their side either, i only remember grouping with one Half elf, 2 Barbarians, a few Iksar.<br>
I have no issues with Humans, Erudites, Trolls and Ogres. Gnomes are on a case by case basis.<br>
Others need to be cleansed.<br>
<br>
Does that make me evil, not in my mind.<br>
Does that make me a Knight, i hope.<br>
<br>
